	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Kaelon:<br />
massmogs should aim to <i>encourage</i> grouping.  The degree to which EQ <i>requires</i> grouping (and uber-guilding at the endgame) is wholly undesireable.<br />
<br />
I love the multiplayer portion of games - but loathe being locked into groups as the only way to advance so that I can experience new content.  If everyone <i>can</i> solo - then no class is required to group. Soloability also creates flexibility in grouping.<br />
<br />
Not only that, but it reduces the time necessary to actually accomplish something.  Organizing groups takes time - and raids take even longer.  If that is the only way to accomplish anything - then short sessions are likewise impossible.<br />
<br />
Encouraging players to group is good.  <br />
Requiring players to work together (group/guild) to obtain certain goals is good.<br />
Requiring players to work together to obtain <i>any</i> goal is a bad thing.<br />
<br />
Tossing around bad political analogies isn't a good idea, but since you started it:<br />
Soloability provides the apex of freedom, liberty and meritocracy.  People will work together when its in their best interest, and when their goals and personalities mesh well.<br />
<br />
Forced grouping is a rigid iron-fisted regime.  You do what you're required to, the way you're required to, as much as you're required to - happiness and preference notwithstanding.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
