	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I love grouping with friends.  But i hate being ~dependent~ on grouping.  This was not so much a problem for my wizard in EQ since i could go kite if i had to, but it was a huge problem for my honey who played a warrior.  If we had realized it when we started, i would have played a cleric just so we'd always be able to start a group with just the 2 of us, but we couldn't and it was very frustrating.  (We started playing with a group of RL friends, and one was already playing a cleric, we didn't consider that we wouldn't always be playing with them.)  WoW sounds very appealing in that since any class can solo, any group makeup will also work.  I can't tell you how many times in EQ there was a group sitting around needing a healer before they could do anything, and how many times i was excluded from guild groups because i could solo but the melee couldn't.  I ~wanted~ to group, but they ~needed~ to group.  It was very depressing for me.<br />
<br />
I don't think that the game needs to make grouping required in order to create socialization.  Humans are social creatures, we will naturally create social structures.  In addition, sometimes i'm PMSing and i'm just really not going to be good company, but i might still want to play.  It's nice to know i'll be able to log on and do some solitary stuff if i want to and not be forced into grouping with people when i'm feeling not so nice.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
