		<!-- message -->
		<div>Uhhm, this really scares me. Im looking forward to a new game as much as you but reading this forum and other wow forums i wonder if wow is the game for me.<br />
<br />
The &quot;you have to group to get anything useful done&quot; aspect of eq is tiresome. Oooh, how it sucks to be lfg an entire evening. But its also one of the greatest things. It makes me meet new wonderful people. It makes me see stuff done in a way that i would never have thought of. <br />
<br />
Soloing all the way to lvl 60. Only grouping with people you know. All this scares me... I wonder if the community will thriwe in a game that is like that.<br />
<br />
I can understand that it seems nice. Maybe all it shows is that wow really isnt the game for me. <br />
<br />
A mmorpg is fun just because i play with other people and use them/get used to gain the most from the game. Soloing, well, i agree with a previous poster that said that there are many other games that are much much better if thats really what i want to do.<br />
<br />
We will see in a few months/years I guess.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
