	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>And is grouping the only way to be social in a MMORPG? This concept of &quot;if you want to solo hunt, play a single player game&quot; is just rather stupid/ignorant statement.<br />
<br />
When I played UO, when I went killing monsters, 95% of the time, it was a solo run for me. Mostly due to the style of which I hunted didnt really leave much time to be &quot;social&quot; as I was constnatly doing something new, or in high-density spawn areas where adding people would of made it harder then easier to do.<br />
<br />
However, I was also very 'soical' in the game. I'd frequent cities and trade/talk with people there. I'd goto player run taverns and towns, roleplay, socalize. I was in a Guild and would frequently pop by the guild house to talk with people, help people train their skills ,show new players around.<br />
<br />
So just because you enjoy doing the hunting/exping/killing aspect alone, does not mean you are not being a social player.<br />
<br />
Also, MMORPGs tend to provide a certian 'buzz' to the game world which makes it come alive, which provides an expierence that most single player games cannot provide.<br />
<br />
People have every right to solo if they want to in a MMORPG, and shouldnt be told &quot;oh, go play a single player game if you want that&quot;</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				...fapfapfap
